			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	Sieging itself never reduces honor, but blockading and declaring wars do. The key point, however, is the power difference. You can lose no honor at all by blockading and warring &quot;fair&quot;, while you will lose a lot by doing the same to easy targets.<br />
<br />
Also, make your Diplomacy CM higher (yes, it's useful stat now), it will lower honor losses.<br />
<br />
Note that this is the first set with honor working from the beginning so it's the first real test of this feature.<br />
<br />
So far I'm attacking players with equal or higher power, grabbing planets and not losing honor. On the other hand I see the top council lost all or most of its points already. So it seems ok :P			   <P align=right></P>
