			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	Any other method will just be open for abuse.  It is a way to keep players honest if they care about the morale thing (doesn't seem to matter much from what I've been able to ascertain).  Just like in real life, it takes a long time to build a bullet proof reputation and only a few blunders to completely wreck it.  If you care about honor then don't randomly blockade players below your power level, and if you don't care, then play like you've always played.<br />
<br />
And finally, I was Bosalian last set and over 80% of my events were bad even though I had a title, 100 honor and Perfect Subject, so the increase in bad events doesn't seem so bad to me, unless maybe that you get double the number of events and they are all bad.			   <P align=right></P>
