			<TD style="background: #333333;" valign=top>
				<IMG src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/posticon.gif" border=0>
				posted 2004-09-29 15:57&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;
				<A href="edit.php?board=player&id=10758"><IMG alt="Edit/Delete Message" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/edit.gif" border=0></A> 
			    <A href="reply.php?board=player&id=10672"><IMG alt="Reply w/Quote" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/quote.gif" border=0></A>
			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	Random events based on space anomalies etc., whether good or bad, aren't based on honor. <br />
But Nova, you haven't seen really BAD events :P <br />
<br />
It's true about the honor rising though. It's how it is supposed to be. It takes a lot of time to build a honor, but little is needed to make you evil.<br />
<br />
If you lose 50 honor with 2 blocks that means that those were very evil blocks :) (ie. you blockaded people half of your power...). In order to avoid becoming evil, you have, most of all, keep you battles fair, meaning, fighting with people of your own power, or higher. Since it seems that most people are complaining about blocks, we might need to lower the loss a bit, but not completly.<br />
<br />
Here's a short tutorial:<br />
<br />
You can lose personal honour by:<br />
- blockading<br />
- declarings wars (esp. if pacted earlier)<br />
- breaking pacts (esp. if allied earlier)<br />
- using deadly special ops (esp. not in war)<br />
- requesting the empire's aid (little)<br />
- submitting to empire's demands (little)<br />
- random events<br />
<br />
You can lose council honour by:<br />
- declaring wars (esp. if pacted earlier)<br />
- breaking pacts (esp. if allied earlier)<br />
- requesting the empire's aid<br />
- accepting members with low honour<br />
<br />
For blocks/wars, you will lose more if the target is lower in power and/or higher in honor, and vice versa. Relation (pact/war etc.) is also relevant. Thus, blockading a random person half of your power is very evil. But blockading a person that is more powerful will make you lose very little. If additionally you have higher honor than that person, you will most likely lose nothing!<br />
<br />
In other words, it is possible to war &quot;fair&quot;, without losing any honor. <br />
<br />
Moreover, Diplomacy CM is very important. This CM is finally useful :) As mentioned in the guide, it reduces honor losses, both personal and council's (using the speaker's CM). With high Diplomacy, you can reduce the loss of all evil acts by up to 50%. Yes, Bosalian speakers are the best. Thus, blockading people later in game will be a bit easier, thanks to better Diplomacy that helps cleaning up mess after evil acts ...<br />
<br />
Personal and council honour values are equally relevant.<br />
<br />
Effects of honour are:<br />
- penalty/bonus to morale in battle<br />
- influence on some good/bad random events<br />
<br />
Note that this makes things like planet milking/trading Evil tactics, but still valid ones.			   <P align=right></P>
			</TD>
		  </TR>

		
