			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	Honor vs. Freezing Bug<br />
<br />
Nevermind the links, they're useless (SSL). I'll try to find them by your IDs. However, I'm quite certain it's not always your honor, but the freezing ships bugs which appears from time to time since a couple of resets, before the honor ever appeared. If your ships don't even fire but just go straight and dissapppear at the edge, or just stop in place before firing/taking any damage, it's not related to honor.<br />
<br />
@Lost<br />
<br />
I did. I said that Nova was right - there is no way to raise the honor by player initiated actions because any such way would be abusable. You could repeat such actions, ie. with a friend, to raise honor artificially. The only way to raise your honor is to keep it from falling, and wait patiently for 2 points per day and random events. If you reached 0 quickly you may think it's impossible to have high honor, but it is. There are plenty of people with high honor, even in top rankings. Just a simple rule of not attacking people lower than you makes you 95% safe from any losses.<br />
<br />
BTW, it's funny that in World of Warcraft, a huge MMORPG by Blizzard, they introduced a similiar honor system, except that they did the mistake we didn't :P ie. when you kill player of lower level, you get negative honor while when you kill player of higher level, you get positive honor (killing in WoW doesn't hurt, so it's like a small battle lost in AS). After 2 or 3 days the honor was disabled, since people immediately started to &quot;farm&quot; honor with cross-faction friends :) See, we're better than Blizzard ;)			   <P align=right></P>
