			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	Penzdragon;<br />
<br />
Your honor dropped to zero by attacking (blockading most likely) players well below your range.  This gave your commanders a false sense of security and now if anyone at all fires at them, they run because they aren't used to meeting resistance.  That's why the military has &quot;live fire&quot; exercises, so that soldiers don't run the first time someone actually fires back at them.<br />
<br />
I also remember people saying that you have to stand up to bullies and they will usually back down, even if you aren't as strong as they are.  I don't know how true that is, but I've heard it an awful lot over the years.  I'm pretty sure that players that gain experience by bullying on players half their power would fall into the bully category.<br />
<br />
So if you stretch the imagination far enough, it doesn't seem quite as silly as you are making it sound.<br />
<br />
embryodead;<br />
<br />
I don't believe that if you siege someone that your honor drops.  I sieged several players at about half my power to protect myself before going to sleep and my honor wasn't affected.  Is this the way it is supposed to be?  I haven't been brave or desperate enough to blockade anyone below my power level, but it might be an interesting experiment for someone else to try to see if honor doesn't drop when you blockade players that you are at war with, even if they are at half your power.			   <P align=right></P>
