			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	Nova<br />
<br />
Sieging doesn't decrease honor. Diplomatic action - that is War Declaration does. So it costs you, or your council (equally relevant), to declare on weaker enemy. But while at war, you can siege at will - seems logical to me.<br />
<br />
Blockades at War have no basic honor &quot;cost&quot;. If the enemy is weaker however, there will be small loss. It might be actually  good idea to reduce honor losses of blocks at War to 0 regardless of power. Doesn't make sense otherwise when compared to siege. Will do... when possible...<br />
<br />
Nice explanation of morale issue BTW :)<br />
<br />
Penz<br />
<br />
The &quot;before even fired&quot; argument isn't a good one, because... well if fleet retreats, it doesn't fire, obviously. The problem is that it either fights or retreats. Hard to balance it - if fleets don't retreat, the system would be useless, if they do, at any point, people complain. I might lower the penalty a bit more, but it's nearing the point of irrelevance =			   <P align=right></P>
			</TD>
